Where should you keep the tapes, for disaster recovery?</TEXT><CHOICEA>in the CIO's office</CHOICEA><CHOICEB>in the Network administrator's desk</CHOICEB><CHOICEC>in a locked safe at an onsite location</CHOICEC><CHOICED>in a locked safe at on offsite location</CHOICED><TYPE>radio</TYPE><ANSWER>D</ANSWER><EXPLANATION>It is best to keep the tapes offsite in case of theft or fire for example.</EXPLANATION></QUESTION></Quiz>

Where should you keep the tapes, for disaster recovery?</TEXT><CHOICEA>in the CIO's office</CHOICEA><CHOICEB>in the Network administrator's desk</CHOICEB><CHOICEC>in a locked safe at an onsite location</CHOICEC><CHOICED>in a locked safe at on offsite location</CHOICED><TYPE>radio</TYPE><ANSWER>D</ANSWER><EXPLANATION>It is best to keep the tapes offsite in case of theft or fire for example.</EXPLANATION></QUESTION></Quiz>
